<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_8a0b0784-ad37-434e-94f9-1301a125e6d2" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>S16C3</sptc><title id="_6322ebaa-9a45-47df-8cee-6cde7f5a2821">Zero depth entry</title><archive-num>2019: Spec D3.10: 3</archive-num><subclause id="_a57bbc1b-96a8-40af-a9e6-88cf330aa374" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_78f13aa8-c12c-4ad3-b02a-d41bc5d6168a">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A zero depth entry must have—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_403cb8ec-29c3-43af-86f8-b6827c7ecacf">a slip-resistant surface; and</li><li id="_7ad16b20-3687-4efd-b490-baf847c4e8fd">a maximum gradient of 1:14; and</li><li id="_19b558d6-4d4b-4ca8-8b4b-cacc198104c9">a single handrail complying with the requirements for handrails in AS 1428.1, from the top of the entry point continuous to the bottom level area; and</li><li id="_a68646ad-8770-4b3d-9b58-2c45c607cb10">a level area—<ol><li>1500 mm long for the width of the zero depth entry at the entry point; and</li><li>located at the bottom of the zero depth entry at a level between 900 mm and 1100 mm below the stationary water level.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause></clause>